data.chText: 熟练的；娴熟的；精通的；训练有素的
data.enText: able to do sth well because of training and practice

data.chText: 我开车的技术还算不错。

data.enText: a high level of oral proficiency in English

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 向前，在前 + fici 做 + ent 具有…性质的 → 在〔别人〕前面做给他们看 → 熟练的

tr: having or showing knowledge and skill and aptitude
example: a lesser-known but no less skillful composer
the effect was achieved by skillful retouching

tr: of or relating to technique or proficiency in a practical skill
example: his technical innovation was his brushwork
the technical dazzle of her dancing

value.def: If you are proficient in something, you can do it well.

example.ex: A great number of Egyptians are proficient in foreign languages.
example.tran: 很多埃及人都精通外语。
